Country fetch using REST Countries API:https://restcountries.com/.
Prerequisites:
Node.js: Ensure that Node.js is installed on your machine. You can download it from the official Node.js website: https://nodejs.org

Setup:
first type :npm init -y on your command
second: npm install express,
third: npm install mongodb

Run:
type node app
open http://localhost:3000 on your brower

You can type country name on the top box then click add it. you should see the country information on your brower.

Each country You can see a button more info, click it you will see more information about your selected country.
